events.description: Roman emperor Elagabalus is murdered alongside his mother, Julia Soaemias. He is replaced by his 14-year old cousin, Severus Alexander.
events.html: • 222 – Roman emperor Elagabalus is murdered alongside his mother, Julia Soaemias. He is replaced by his 14-year old cousin, Severus Alexander.[1][2]

events.description: The Battle of Badr, the first major battle between the Muslims and Quraysh.
events.html: • 624 – The Battle of Badr, the first major battle between the Muslims and Quraysh.[3]

events.description: Siege of Warangal: Sultan Ghiyath al-Din Tughluq sends an expeditionary army led by his son, Muhammad bin Tughluq, to the Kakatiya capital Warangal
events.html: • 1323 – Siege of Warangal: Sultan Ghiyath al-Din Tughluq sends an expeditionary army led by his son, Muhammad bin Tughluq, to the Kakatiya capital Warangal – after ruler Prataparudra has refused to make tribute payments. He besieges the city and finally, after a campaign of 8 months, Prataparudra surrenders on November 9.[4]

events.description: The Battle of Oosterweel, traditionally regarded as the start of the Eighty Years' War.
events.html: • 1567 – The Battle of Oosterweel, traditionally regarded as the start of the Eighty Years' War.[5]

events.description: At the Battle of Tondibi in Mali, Moroccan forces of the Saadi dynasty, led by Judar Pasha, defeat the Songhai Empire, despite being outnumbered by at least five to one.
events.html: • 1591 – At the Battle of Tondibi in Mali, Moroccan forces of the Saadi dynasty, led by Judar Pasha, defeat the Songhai Empire, despite being outnumbered by at least five to one.[6]

events.description: Harvard College is named after clergyman John Harvard.
events.html: • 1639 – Harvard College is named after clergyman John Harvard.[7]

events.description: Nojpetén, capital of the last independent Maya kingdom, falls to Spanish conquistadors, the final step in the Spanish conquest of Guatemala.
events.html: • 1697 – Nojpetén, capital of the last independent Maya kingdom, falls to Spanish conquistadors, the final step in the Spanish conquest of Guatemala.[8]

events.description: The Battle of Cartagena de Indias (part of the War of Jenkins' Ear) begins.
events.html: • 1741 – The Battle of Cartagena de Indias (part of the War of Jenkins' Ear) begins.[9]

events.description: William Herschel discovers Uranus.
events.html: • 1781 – William Herschel discovers Uranus.[10]

events.description: Gustav IV Adolf of Sweden is deposed in the Coup of 1809.
events.html: • 1809 – Gustav IV Adolf of Sweden is deposed in the Coup of 1809.[11]

events.description: A French and Italian fleet is defeated by a British squadron off the island of Vis in the Adriatic during the Napoleonic Wars.
events.html: • 1811 – A French and Italian fleet is defeated by a British squadron off the island of Vis in the Adriatic during the Napoleonic Wars.[12]

events.description: Participants at the Congress of Vienna declare Napoleon an outlaw following his escape from Elba
events.html: • 1815 – Participants at the Congress of Vienna declare Napoleon an outlaw following his escape from Elba[13]

events.description: Pope Leo XII publishes the apostolic constitution Quo Graviora in which he renewed the prohibition on Catholics joining freemasonry.
events.html: • 1826 – Pope Leo XII publishes the apostolic constitution Quo Graviora in which he renewed the prohibition on Catholics joining freemasonry.[14]

events.description: Felix Mendelssohn's Violin Concerto receives its première performance in Leipzig with Ferdinand David as soloist.
events.html: • 1845 – Felix Mendelssohn's Violin Concerto receives its première performance in Leipzig with Ferdinand David as soloist.[15]

events.description: The German revolutions of 1848–1849 begin in Vienna.
events.html: • 1848 – The German revolutions of 1848–1849 begin in Vienna.[16]

events.description: The Act Prohibiting the Return of Slaves is passed by the United States Congress, effectively annulling the Fugitive Slave Act of 1850 and setting the stage for the Emancipation Proclamation.
events.html: • 1862 – The Act Prohibiting the Return of Slaves is passed by the United States Congress, effectively annulling the Fugitive Slave Act of 1850 and setting the stage for the Emancipation Proclamation.[17]

entities.name: Act Prohibiting the Return of Slaves

events.description: The Siege of Khartoum begins. It lasts until January 26, 1885.
events.html: • 1884 – The Siege of Khartoum begins. It lasts until January 26, 1885.[18]

events.description: The eruption of Ritter Island triggers tsunamis that kill up to 3,000 people on nearby islands.
events.html: • 1888 – The eruption of Ritter Island triggers tsunamis that kill up to 3,000 people on nearby islands.[19]

events.description: British forces occupy Bloemfontein, Orange Free State, during the Second Boer War.
events.html: • 1900 – British forces occupy Bloemfontein, Orange Free State, during the Second Boer War.[20]

events.description: The Kapp Putsch briefly ousts the Weimar Republic government from Berlin.
events.html: • 1920 – The Kapp Putsch briefly ousts the Weimar Republic government from Berlin.[21]

events.description: The news of the discovery of Pluto is announced by Lowell Observatory.
events.html: • 1930 – The news of the discovery of Pluto is announced by Lowell Observatory.[22]

events.description: The Winter War between Finland and the Soviet Union officially ends after the signing of the Moscow Peace Treaty.
events.html: • 1940 – The Winter War between Finland and the Soviet Union officially ends after the signing of the Moscow Peace Treaty.[23]

events.description: The Holocaust: German forces liquidate the Jewish ghetto in Kraków.
events.html: • 1943 – The Holocaust: German forces liquidate the Jewish ghetto in Kraków.[24]

events.description: The Battle of Điện Biên Phủ begins with an artillery barrage by Viet Minh forces under Võ Nguyên Giáp; Viet Minh victory led to the end of the First Indochina War and French withdrawal from Vietnam.
events.html: • 1954 – The Battle of Điện Biên Phủ begins with an artillery barrage by Viet Minh forces under Võ Nguyên Giáp; Viet Minh victory led to the end of the First Indochina War and French withdrawal from Vietnam.[25]

events.description: Cuban student revolutionaries storm the presidential palace in Havana in a failed attempt on the life of President Fulgencio Batista.
events.html: • 1957 – Cuban student revolutionaries storm the presidential palace in Havana in a failed attempt on the life of President Fulgencio Batista.[26]

events.description: Apollo 9 returns safely to Earth after testing the Lunar Module.
events.html: • 1969 – Apollo 9 returns safely to Earth after testing the Lunar Module.[27]

events.description: Sierra Pacific Airlines Flight 802 crashes into the White Mountains near Bishop, California, killing 36.
events.html: • 1974 – Sierra Pacific Airlines Flight 802 crashes into the White Mountains near Bishop, California, killing 36.[28]

events.description: The New Jewel Movement, headed by Maurice Bishop, ousts the Prime Minister of Grenada, Eric Gairy, in a coup d'état.
events.html: • 1979 – The New Jewel Movement, headed by Maurice Bishop, ousts the Prime Minister of Grenada, Eric Gairy, in a coup d'état.[29]

entities.name: List of heads of government of Grenada

events.description: The Seikan Tunnel, the longest tunnel in the world with an undersea segment, opens between Aomori and Hakodate, Japan.
events.html: • 1988 – The Seikan Tunnel, the longest tunnel in the world with an undersea segment, opens between Aomori and Hakodate, Japan.[30]

events.description: The Mw  6.6 Erzincan earthquake strikes eastern Turkey with a maximum Mercalli intensity of VIII (Severe).
events.html: • 1992 – The Mw  6.6 Erzincan earthquake strikes eastern Turkey with a maximum Mercalli intensity of VIII (Severe).[31]

events.description: The 1993 Storm of the Century affects the eastern United States, dropping feet of snow in many areas.
events.html: • 1993 – The 1993 Storm of the Century affects the eastern United States, dropping feet of snow in many areas.[32]

events.description: The Dunblane massacre leads to the death of sixteen primary school children and one teacher in Dunblane, Scotland.
events.html: • 1996 – The Dunblane massacre leads to the death of sixteen primary school children and one teacher in Dunblane, Scotland.[33]

events.description: The Missionaries of Charity choose Sister Nirmala to succeed Mother Teresa as their leader.
events.html: • 1997 – The Missionaries of Charity choose Sister Nirmala to succeed Mother Teresa as their leader.[34]

events.description: An article in Nature identifies the Ciampate del Diavolo as 350,000-year-old hominid footprints.
events.html: • 2003 – An article in Nature identifies the Ciampate del Diavolo as 350,000-year-old hominid footprints.[35]

events.description: The Sierre coach crash kills 28 people, including 22 children.
events.html: • 2012 – The Sierre coach crash kills 28 people, including 22 children.[36]

events.description: The 2013 papal conclave elects Cardinal Jorge Mario Bergoglio taking the name Pope Francis as the 266th Pope of the Catholic Church.
events.html: • 2013 – The 2013 papal conclave elects Cardinal Jorge Mario Bergoglio taking the name Pope Francis as the 266th Pope of the Catholic Church.[37]

events.description: The Ankara bombing kills at least 37 people.
events.html: • 2016 – The Ankara bombing kills at least 37 people.[38]

events.description: Three gunmen attack two hotels in the Ivory Coast town of Grand-Bassam, killing at least 19 people.
events.html: • 2016 – Three gunmen attack two hotels in the Ivory Coast town of Grand-Bassam, killing at least 19 people.[39]
